h3. Problem summary

The *Select List (cascading)* field type is currently not supposed in Automation for Jira.

h3. Workaround

Workaround from https://support.atlassian.com/jira-software-cloud/docs/advanced-field-editing-json/#field-syntax-examples:
{code}
{
   "fields": {
  "First Field" : { "value": "First value", "child": { "value" : "Child value"} }
    }
}
{code}

h3. Issue Summary

According to the documentation to [Bulk create issues via REST API (POST /rest/api/3/issue/bulk)|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/?&_ga=2.193505389.1741017122.1586342626-1080961822.1564054573#api-rest-api-3-issue-bulk-post], you should be able to transition them as well but this is not working.

The issues are correctly created, no error returned, but they do not transition to the given status.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a project (e.g. TEST)
 # Send a POST request to the /rest/api/3/issue/bulk endpoint in order to bulk create and transition issues using a body like the below one:
{noformat}
{
  "issueUpdates": [
    {
      "transition": {
        "id": "11"
      },	
      "fields": {
        "project": {
          "key": "TEST"
        },
        "summary": "Test Bulk Create REST 2",
        "issuetype": {
          "name": "Task",
          "subtask": false
        },
        "priority": {
          "name": "High"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "transition": {
        "id": "11"
      },		
      "fields": {
        "project": {
          "key": "TEST"
        },
        "summary": "TEST bulk creation REST API ",
        "issuetype": {
          "name": "Task",
          "subtask": false
        },
        "priority": {
          "name": "Medium"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results

The issues are crated and transitioned to the desired status
h3. Actual Results

The issues are created. No error is returned, but there was no transition. The issues are still in their initial status.
h3. Workaround

Transition the issues after they have been created by using the [Transition issue|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/?&_ga=2.193505389.1741017122.1586342626-1080961822.1564054573#api-rest-api-3-issue-issueIdOrKey-transitions-post] (POST /rest/api/3/issue/\{issueIdOrKey}/transitions) endpoint

I'm using the v3 API for getting information about issues, including the sprint status. I want to get the active sprint associated with the issue for a report.


When using the /search endpoint, I don't get a sprint object like the v1 API did, but it's a custom field (customfield_10008 in my case) and an array of "weird-looking" values like: 
{code:java}
com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint@23fe62a9[id=80,rapidViewId=3,state=CLOSED,name=Week 8,goal=,startDate=2020-02-17T09:56:05.521Z,endDate=2020-02-24T09:56:00.000Z,completeDate=2020-02-24T09:38:24.325Z,sequence=80]
{code}
I can write a regex expression for this, but in my opinion that's not the way it should work. FOr the record: I'm using PHP.

{panel:title=Atlassian Update - 14 October 2020|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#2684ff|titleBGColor=#2684ff|bgColor=#ffffff}
Hi everyone, thank you for your interest surrounding this ticket. Before we begin [transitioning all users to the new issue view|https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Jira-articles/Transitioning-all-Jira-Cloud-users-to-the-new-issue-view/ba-p/1494104] on 31 March, 2021, we’ll be solving this problem. Watch this ticket for updates as we progress and please add a comment for any questions you may have.
{panel}

New issue view is missing with *Remaining estimate* field  and does not have an option for configuration under Issue layout. 

Work around : 
Use the old issue view to update the Remaining estimate field.
